headline: AM Best Downgrades Credit Ratings of Humana Health of Puerto Rico Group’s Subsidiaries; Affirms Credit Ratings of Humana Inc. and Most of Its Health Insurance Subsidiaries
summary: OLDWICK, N.J., December 05, 2024--AM Best has downgraded the Financial Strength Rating (FSR) to B+ (Good) from B++ (Good) and the Long-Term Issuer Credit Rating (Long-Term ICR) to "bbb-" (Good) from "bbb" (Good) of Humana Insurance of Puerto Rico, Inc. and Humana Health Plans of Puerto Rico, Inc. These companies are domiciled in Puerto Rico and collectively are referred to as Humana Health of Puerto Rico Group. headline: Humana: Medicare Advantage Is Just A Short-Term Problem
summary: Humana's stock has declined 18% while the S&P 500 returned 13.5%, driven by short-term issues with Medicare Advantage. Learn why I am still bullish on HUM.
